Database - Any collection of related data 

Database Management System (DMBS) - Special software that helps users create and maintain a database (MySQL) 

It makes it easy to store large amounts of information, handles security, backups and can interact with software.  

The DMBS is not the actual database, but the software application that creates stores and deletes information. When interacting with a database, you are not programming the database directly, rather telling the database management system what to do.  

CRUD - Create, Read, Update, Delete 

These are the main 4 operations of the database management system  

Relational Databases (SQL) - Organise data into one or more tables, each table has columns and rows and a unique key identifies each row.  

Structured Query Language - SQL 

Standardised language for interacting with RDBMS 

Used to perform CRUD operations, and other tasks such as security and backup 

Used to define tables and structures 

SQL code on one RDBMS is not always portable to another without modifications.  

Database Queries - A request that is made to the DBMS for specific information.
